            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once hot, add your <strong>toasted sesame oil </strong>with the <strong>chopped green beans</strong>, <strong>remaining chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the beans are beginning to soften</p><p>Tip: Add a drizzle of<strong> </strong>vegetable oil if it's looking a little dry!</p><p>Once beginning to soften, add the <strong>spinach </strong>and cook for 1-2 min further or until wilted – these are your <strong>sesame greens</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700645032873-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1700645032873-x400.jpg",
